root.limiter: MO STATE BLSTATE BLO BLA LMO BTS CONF /any/ \n{2,}
root.HEADER: RADIO X-CEIVER ADMINISTRATION MANAGED OBJECT STATUS

BLO.b0: Object blocked from own supervision permanently.
BLO.b1: Object blocked from own supervision temporarily.
BLO.b2: Object blocked due to fault suspected.
BLO.b6: Object blocked from Operations and Maintenance Link (OML).
BLO.b8: Object blocked due to local maintenance activities.
BLO.b9: Object blocked from Central Functions (CF) or Sector Central Functions (SCF).
BLO.b10: Object blocked due to local mode.
BLO.b11: Object blocked due to loop test failure.
BLO.b12: CF blocked due to transmission mode incompatibility.
BLO.b13: Object blocked due to power savings.
BLO.b15: Object block from Antenna Integrated Radio (AIR).

BLA.b0: Object needs reset and unconditional load or reset and loading are in progress.
BLA.b1: Object needs reset and load check or the reset and loading are in progress.
BLA.b2: Object needs load check or loading in progress.
BLA.b3: Object needs polling or polling in progress.
BLA.b4: Object needs testing or testing in progress.
BLA.b5: Object needs intermittent test or intermittent test in progress.
BLA.b6: Object needs reset or reset in progress.
BLA.b8: Object needs to be manually unblocked due to request from the Base Transceiver Station (BTS).
BLA.b9: Object needs loop test or loop test in progress.

LMO.b5: LRX blocked due to creation in progress.
LMO.b6: LRX blocked due to not enabled.
